TopicTitle: KeyNotFoundException: All is well except textures in partlab

Articles.Content:
Following Epsilon\'s blender guide, I decide I would try my hand at making a command pod. After completing all of the steps fully, including the post-scriptum which caused my other pod to fail, I discovered that the pod was not showing up textured. Several loads through partlab revealed similar results. This error was displayed in the box on the top left corner of the program: KeyNotFoundException: The given key was not present in the dictionary

Here is an image.

I have also included the part in a ZIP below to see if anyone can get it to work. The Pod was built in Blender, textures are 32-bit from Paint.NET.

Also, the textures are intentionally horrible.
